eNCA reporter Heidi Giokos is following this story. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Despite unpleasant weather conditions, City Power is working tirelessly in efforts to restore electricity in the CBD by the end of Sunday. Selby and surrounding areas in the Joburg CBD have been without electricity for over five days and counting. This follows an underground fire that destroyed the main power lines. READ: City Power apologises for extended outage City Power has already begun repairs with the laying of new cables but it’s unclear when power will be fully restored. eNCA reporter Heidi Giokos shares more details in the video above.